It’s all about building up your colours! I first start by creating a base color, knowing that I want my end shade to be a emerald Jade colour. I know I’m looking for a rich green with a dominant blue shade popping through 🌈 

Building your colours up also allows you to use less colouring. If I were to just add in blue and green, I would have to use a TON to get this same shade and cancel out any undertone colours. However when I take the time to build up a base colour, then change my tone by adding additional colours on top. I end up using way less  gels and still have a vivid shade 🤗 Let me know if you found this helpful

Tips on how to create the perfect stripes, tips below 👇 
Also letting the cat out of the bag, I’m planning on filming my first YouTube video on this topic in October 🎉 
A full how to tutorial type of video ( been putting off YouTube forever cause it scares me 😂) anyways ….

⭐️ stripe tips ⭐️ 
Before ANYTHING else make sure your layers are as straight as you can get them! This helps so much when you’re scraping off your stripes. If your cake sides are all uneven, you end up scraping away more buttercream from one area then the other 😑 which is so so hard to fix! 

⭐️ pipe the stripes one at a time instead of icing the whole cake and having to scrape off more then half of the buttercream. In my opinion it creates twice as much work and mess. 

⭐️ let it chill in your freezer for 15 mins or until you can touch the buttercream and it doesn’t come off in your finger. Fill in your colours and start scraping right away, since the cake is chilled you don’t want to let the new buttercream sit to long or it becomes harder to move around the cake 

⭐️ once you are happy with your stripes, run your cake comb under hot water and go around slowly in one motion 🤗 
Let me know below if this help 😘
